# TrueBlocks API Blueprint

The TrueBlocks API is designed to expose data generated from `trueblocks-core` along with a local Ethereum node. Among other things, it facilitates account history queries.

## Export Transaction Records for Address [/export{?maxBlocks}{?ripe}{?unripe}{?noBlooms}{?staging}{?start}{?address_list}{?fmt}{?articulate}{?logs}{?blocks}{?txs}{?traces}{?ddos}{?maxTraces}{?start}{?end}]

A resource that tells trueblocks that you want to export transactions for `address`. Trueblocks will use its appearance index to ask the node for detailed information about each appearance. The information is then returned in either JSON or CSV.

+ Parameters

    + maxBlocks:  (optional, <val>) - scan at most --maxBlocks blocks ('all' implies scan to end of chain)
    + ripe:  (optional, boolean) - visit ripe (old enough, but not yet staged or finalized) blocks
    + unripe:  (optional, boolean) - visit unripe (not old enough and not yet staged or finalized) blocks
    + noBlooms:  (optional, boolean) - turn off bloom filters for performance testing
    + staging:  (optional, boolean) - produce results in the staging folder instead of production folder
    + start:  (optional, <num>) - first block to check
    + address_list:  (optional, boolean) - one or more addresses (0x...) to export
    + fmt:  (optional, <fmt>) - export format (one of [json|txt|csv])
    + articulate:  (optional, boolean) - articulate transactions, traces, logs, and outputs
    + logs:  (optional, boolean) - export logs instead of transactions
    + blocks:  (optional, <on/off>) - write blocks to the binary cache ('off' by default)
    + txs:  (optional, <on/off>) - write transactions to the binary cache ('on' by default)
    + traces:  (optional, <on/off>) - write traces to the binary cache ('off' by default)
    + ddos:  (optional, <on/off>) - skip over dDos transactions in export ('on' by default)
    + maxTraces:  (optional, <num>) - if --ddos:on, the number of traces defining a dDos (default = 250)
    + start:  (optional, <num>) - first block to export (inclusive)
    + end:  (optional, <num>) - last block to export (inclusive)

