## View block detail [/block{?block_list}{?hash_only}{?check}{?addrs}{?uniq}{?uniqTx}{?number}{?filter}{?latest}{?force}{?quiet}{?source}{?fields}{?normalize}]

Look at a block.

+ Parameters

    + block_list:  (optional, boolean) - a space-separated list of one or more blocks to retrieve
    + hash_only:  (optional, boolean) - display only transaction hashes, default is to display full transaction detail
    + check:  (optional, boolean) - compare results between qblocks and Ethereum node, report differences, if any
    + addrs:  (optional, boolean) - display all addresses included in the block
    + uniq:  (optional, boolean) - display only uniq addresses found per block
    + uniqTx:  (optional, boolean) - display only uniq addresses found per transaction
    + number:  (optional, boolean) - display address counts (alterntively --addrCnt, --uniqTxCnt, or --uniqCnt)
    + filter:  (optional, <addr>) - useful only for --addrs or --uniq, only display this address in results
    + latest:  (optional, boolean) - display the latest blocks at both the node and the cache
    + force:  (optional, boolean) - force a re-write of the block to the cache
    + quiet:  (optional, boolean) - do not print results to screen, used for speed testing and data checking
    + source:  (optional, [c|r]) - either :c(a)che or :(r)aw, source for data retrival. (shortcuts -c = qblocks, -r = node)
    + fields:  (optional, [a|m|c|r]) - either :(a)ll, (m)ini, (c)ache or :(r)aw; which fields to include in output (all is default)
    + normalize:  (optional, boolean) - normalize (remove un-common fields and sort) for comparison with other results (testing)

